article.headline: Kennesaw State 85, W. Illinois 63
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- Kurtis Woods scored 19 points to help Kennesaw State rout Western Illinois 85-63 on Friday night. Woods connected on 6-of-7 shots from the floor and made five 3-pointers for the Owls (1-0), who won for the first time on opening night since 2004. J.D. Pollock scored 16 points and John-Michael Nickerson added 15 points. Seven different Kennesaw State players hit 3-pointers, as the Owls connected on 16-of-28 3-pointers from beyond the arc. The Owls shot 54 percent from the field and had eight blocks. David DuBois scored 18 points for Western Illinois (0-1), while Quenton Kirby added 17 points and eight rebounds.
